ce:section.ce:para:
In this study, we have designed a ratiometric sensing strategy for simultaneous detection of Cu(II) and ALP with high selectivity and sensitivity using functionalized Pdots as fluorescence signal transduction. The highly fluorescent Pdots were prepared with Poly[(9,9-dioctylfluorenyl-2,7-diyl)-co-(1,4-benzo-{2,1′,3}-thiadiazole)] (PFBT) via nanoprecipitation and then assembled with non-fluorescent Rhodamine B hydrazide (RB-hy), which shows special binding activity to Cu(Ⅱ), to obtain functionalized nanohybrids Pdots@RB-hy through electrostatic and hydrophobic interactions. In the presence of Cu(II), a coordinated reaction between Cu(II) and RB-hy assembled onto Pdots occurred and fluorescent coordinated complexes, RB-hy-Cu(II) were formed. As thus, a FRET donors/acceptors pair was constructed in which PFBT Pdots act as energy donors while RB-hy-Cu(II) complexes act as energy acceptors. On the basis of the varies in fluorescence intensities of donors/acceptors of FRET system in the presence of different amounts of Cu(II), a ratiometric method for sensing Cu(II) was proposed (

                     Scheme 1
                     ).
